    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A humming noise without the fan spinning on your AC unit is a classic sign of a mechanical issue, like a seized motor or a capacitor failure. It's not entirely safe to just poke around it without knowing what you're dealing with, especially if you're not familiar with electrical components. It's much safer to have a qualified HVAC technician take a look, as these units can have high voltage, and you don't want to accidentally become part of the next big, noisy, and potentially dangerous, problem. Calling a professional is the wisest move here.",
